WEBVTT

00:02.086 --> 00:04.420
Previously on Justified...

00:05.089 --> 00:06.631
- Evening.
- Where's Ellen May?

00:06.757 --> 00:09.926
One of my deputies
saw a girl who fits Ellen May's description

00:10.135 --> 00:11.928
get waved over to an 18-wheeler.

00:14.598 --> 00:16.432
- Damn it!
- I don't know where Ellen May is,

00:16.558 --> 00:18.559
and your smacking me around
ain't gonna change that!

00:18.644 --> 00:21.020
I swear I am not Drew Thompson.

00:21.105 --> 00:22.397
That's not what Arlo Givens says.

00:22.481 --> 00:24.607
Well, Arlo Givens is a lying sack of shit!

00:25.150 --> 00:28.277
I don't know why Josiah told you
Drew's still up here.

00:28.445 --> 00:30.863
Only time I seen him
since he left was near 10 years ago

00:30.948 --> 00:32.490
at the bluegrass festival,

00:32.616 --> 00:35.076
rubbing shoulders with the mayor,
judge executive.

00:35.160 --> 00:37.745
All them rich Clover Hill folks.

00:37.830 --> 00:40.707
How do you think
we're gonna get into Napier's party?

00:40.791 --> 00:42.625
He'd shoot me before I got through the door.

00:42.960 --> 00:45.503
Not if we use Arnold to get us an invite.

00:45.963 --> 00:47.171
I'll handle Napier.

00:47.631 --> 00:49.924
You just consider yourself invited.
Both of you.

00:50.259 --> 00:52.635
Jody Adair,
charged with double homicide.

00:52.928 --> 00:54.804
He's got an ex-wife in Lexington.

00:54.972 --> 00:57.640
You put eyes on him,
I'll make it worth your while.

01:00.144 --> 01:01.644
This could be a little uncomfortable.

01:01.812 --> 01:03.229
Just be cool and go with it.

01:03.313 --> 01:06.482
I get out of these,
I'll tear you to pieces small enough to flush.

01:06.775 --> 01:09.193
Look, I ain't here on Marshals' business.

01:09.695 --> 01:11.988
I just want to know
about the man in the trunk.

01:23.167 --> 01:25.209
Unconstitutional, man. I got to piss.

01:25.335 --> 01:27.628
ACLU be happy to take up your case.

01:27.713 --> 01:30.173
- Let's go, brother.
- Suck my dick, brother.

01:32.468 --> 01:33.634
Nice work, Givens.

01:34.178 --> 01:35.803
Always looking to fill up the piggy bank.

01:36.054 --> 01:37.680
As you like it.

01:38.307 --> 01:40.224
Besides, a good man's hard to find.

01:40.350 --> 01:42.310
I don't know what to say.
You found me so easy.

01:42.853 --> 01:44.187
Your cell still best?

01:44.354 --> 01:46.564
If you're in town,
just stop by the High Note Bar.

01:46.690 --> 01:48.149
Pretty well living there these days.

01:49.401 --> 01:51.319
I hope you're not drinking away your wages.

01:51.403 --> 01:53.362
It would ravage those Hollywood looks.

01:53.739 --> 01:56.240
- We good, Sharon?
- We're good, Raylan.

01:56.533 --> 01:58.534
- It's good to see you.
- Likewise.

02:01.747 --> 02:05.708
Playing behind the beat, all cool,
making the girl do all the flirting.

02:06.084 --> 02:08.252
Shit only flies
if you're a pretty boy like Eastwood there.

02:08.377 --> 02:10.003
See, Raylan there, he's got the badge

02:10.088 --> 02:12.840
and the drawl
and the whole squinty, sexy thing,

02:12.925 --> 02:15.259
and there was a time
I would have run right to him,

02:15.385 --> 02:17.053
done the whole merry-go-round.

02:17.221 --> 02:19.597
Now I see that for what it is, and

02:20.724 --> 02:22.517
him for who he is.

02:23.685 --> 02:25.853
That man's an emotional disaster.

02:26.230 --> 02:27.855
Sharon, you gonna die an old maid.

02:30.400 --> 02:31.692
What is that?

02:33.862 --> 02:35.404
Looks like we lost the rear tyre.

02:38.408 --> 02:39.909
Be a doll and fix it.

02:40.077 --> 02:41.744
- You gonna get all girly on me now?
- Girly?

02:41.870 --> 02:44.580
Honey, I'm gonna cop a squat.
You know I drank all 36 ounces.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.749
Mr Pibb?
Lord, how do you drink any ounces?

02:46.875 --> 02:48.459
Nectar of the gods.

02:54.466 --> 02:56.092
Yeah, make it snappy.

03:09.439 --> 03:10.940
What's up, man? You need a hand?

03:11.066 --> 03:12.316
All good, friend.

03:12.734 --> 03:14.652
I got AAA. If you want, I can make a call.

03:14.778 --> 03:16.404
They'll be here in 20, 30 minutes.

03:16.613 --> 03:17.905
It's time to move on.

03:19.908 --> 03:21.200
- You understand?
- Yeah.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.452
Some thanks I get
for being a Good Samaritan.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.788
I don't mean no offence. For your own safety.

03:26.415 --> 03:28.082
All right.

04:07.831 --> 04:09.749
- Where is she?
- You said poke out the tyre,

04:09.833 --> 04:10.917
which I did when they got food,

04:11.001 --> 04:12.877
but you didn't say anything
about killing nobody!

04:13.003 --> 04:14.337
Tell me where she went.

04:15.047 --> 04:16.380
I'm just a filmmaker.

04:18.007 --> 04:19.382
Kennet!

04:20.510 --> 04:23.554
You don't tell me where she went,
I'll kill your ass.

04:42.407 --> 04:43.491
Kennet!

05:24.199 --> 05:25.324
Already signed that.

05:26.284 --> 05:28.077
Dunlop's birthday card.

05:28.412 --> 05:30.955
This is the summary
of those 20 boxes they gave us.

05:31.039 --> 05:34.166
- It's bullshit.
- That's not just bullshit, Raylan.

05:34.251 --> 05:36.961
That is rare, vintage FBI bullshit.

05:37.045 --> 05:38.254
That's a whole different bouquet.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.548
Drew Thompson is a 30-year-old case.

05:40.632 --> 05:42.216
They expect us to believe that?

05:42.300 --> 05:45.011
I tried to call Barkley
and chew his ass out about it,

05:45.095 --> 05:47.555
but he's been AWOL for a few days.
Hasn't been to work.

05:47.639 --> 05:49.890
Since when does
J. Edgar Barkley miss work?

05:49.975 --> 05:51.350
Anyway, we don't need the FBI.

05:51.435 --> 05:53.936
We can dig ourselves
through all those Clover Hill names

05:54.021 --> 05:57.148
that your cousin Mary
and the one-legged man gave us.

05:57.315 --> 05:59.191
One-footed. Still got most of his leg.

05:59.276 --> 06:02.319
You're doing that thing that makes me
believe you don't have high hopes.

06:02.529 --> 06:03.988
- That eyebrow thing?
- Yeah.

06:04.948 --> 06:06.532
'Cause I don't have high hopes.

06:07.492 --> 06:08.826
I mean, what have we got?

06:08.952 --> 06:12.705
We got 20 worthless boxes
and the Hill woman's riddles

06:12.873 --> 06:15.541
and the ravings of a one-footed man.

06:15.709 --> 06:17.043
Tell me we shouldn't lose hope.

06:17.169 --> 06:18.919
- We shouldn't lose hope.
- Why not?

06:19.087 --> 06:21.881
Well, maybe that
psychic friend of yours, Eve Munro,

06:22.007 --> 06:24.425
she could look through
all those DMV photos of everybody

06:24.509 --> 06:27.053
that fits Drew's description
and maybe hit the jackpot.

06:27.137 --> 06:28.637
Good Lord.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.931
You know,
instead of just sitting around here...

06:31.016 --> 06:32.475
- I ain't going.
- Just hear me out.

06:32.559 --> 06:35.519
I don't want to see Arlo,
let alone have that same conversation.

06:35.645 --> 06:37.354
I'm not saying go see your father.

06:37.481 --> 06:39.648
I'm saying go down to Tramble

06:39.733 --> 06:42.026
and talk to that guy
who used to be the Harlan sheriff.

06:42.152 --> 06:43.569
- Hunter.
- Right.

06:43.862 --> 06:45.821
One-footed Josiah mentioned him, didn't he?

06:45.947 --> 06:47.031
He did.

06:47.115 --> 06:50.242
Well, just go talk to him, and then after that,
go talk to your father.

06:50.327 --> 06:51.368
Art...

06:51.495 --> 06:52.870
He knows who and where Drew is.

06:52.996 --> 06:54.663
- He won't...
- It's easy, Raylan.

06:54.790 --> 06:55.873
You just stuff that file,

06:55.999 --> 06:57.958
tell him we've got
all the evidence that we need,

06:58.043 --> 06:59.627
and then you give him a little nudge

06:59.836 --> 07:01.921
or a thinly veiled threat, and he'll spook.

07:02.047 --> 07:03.130
He won't.

07:03.215 --> 07:04.507
Well, then you give him a sob story.

07:04.591 --> 07:06.717
You know, tell him you don't
want to see him die in prison.

07:07.511 --> 07:10.012
Raylan, go see your father.

07:13.558 --> 07:15.893
Where do we keep
the folder for take-out menus?

07:15.977 --> 07:17.686
Over by the copy machine.

07:18.730 --> 07:19.855
You working lunch?

07:20.065 --> 07:21.732
Go get 'em, tiger!

07:25.112 --> 07:26.612
Happy birthday, Nelson.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.572
Thanks, Raylan.

07:29.741 --> 07:30.825
Believe that?

07:30.909 --> 07:32.034
He wished me a happy birthday.

07:32.119 --> 07:34.954
Jesus Christ, Nelson.
I'm sorry I forgot your birthday.

07:40.001 --> 07:41.710
It's nice just laying here.

07:43.088 --> 07:44.213
Feel safe.

07:44.756 --> 07:48.425
That boy that beat on you the other day,
I gave him a whooping he won't soon forget.

07:50.345 --> 07:52.054
I didn't like doing it.

07:53.348 --> 07:56.559
But it needed doing. For you.

07:57.727 --> 07:59.520
You ain't just saying that?

08:01.231 --> 08:03.440
You are not like the other girls.

08:04.276 --> 08:06.235
You got a light in your eyes.

08:06.653 --> 08:08.904
I'd be lying
if I said I didn't feel that way about you

08:08.989 --> 08:10.197
the first time I saw you.

08:10.866 --> 08:13.951
Wasn't two days ago
you were all up in my face.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.911
Now you come over
and get something-something

08:15.996 --> 08:17.538
and you want to romance me, too?

08:18.039 --> 08:20.249
Just tell me what you want.

08:21.126 --> 08:22.459
Hey.

08:23.920 --> 08:26.213
I want to know who put the hurt on you.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.382
It wasn't Max, so who?

08:28.758 --> 08:30.176
What do you care?

08:32.636 --> 08:33.929
See, now...

08:34.972 --> 08:38.601
I didn't know it wasn't Max 100%,
but right there, you just made me sure of it.

08:38.684 --> 08:40.269
Shit, Johnny.

08:40.604 --> 08:42.730
So, who could it be?

08:44.274 --> 08:47.276
Who do I know and you know

08:47.736 --> 08:50.487
could scare you into shutting up?

08:52.490 --> 08:55.993
Damn it, Johnny. Leave it alone.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.457
Was it Colt?

09:02.834 --> 09:04.752
Yeah, it was Colt.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.337
I did not say that name.

09:06.504 --> 09:08.881
- No, you did not.
- You swear on that.

09:08.965 --> 09:11.133
He said he'd cut out my damn tongue.

09:11.760 --> 09:13.093
Now, why would he say something like that,

09:13.178 --> 09:15.721
not to mention
beat you and scare you half to death?

09:15.847 --> 09:19.433
He was tweaking and pissed off,
asking about Ellen May.

09:21.394 --> 09:22.728
Ellen May?

09:23.271 --> 09:26.065
Where she is or did she call or some shit.

09:26.733 --> 09:29.610
Forget exactly.
He kind of punched me right after.

09:37.786 --> 09:40.079
I meant what I said, Teri.

09:48.838 --> 09:50.130
- Givens.
- Deputy Givens,

09:50.215 --> 09:52.299
Loren Hunkis,
Campbell county sheriff's deputy.

09:52.384 --> 09:54.843
- How can I help you?
- You were one of the last incoming calls

09:54.928 --> 09:56.595
on the cell phone of Sharon Edmunds.

09:56.721 --> 09:58.764
Can you tell me
what association you had with her.

09:58.848 --> 09:59.890
Had?

09:59.975 --> 10:02.851
Fished her van out of Norris Lake
around 6:00 this morning.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.521
Two bodies in the vehicle,
one of which was Ms Edmunds.

10:05.605 --> 10:06.689
Damn.

10:06.773 --> 10:09.108
Decomp suggests
they've been dead about six days.

10:09.234 --> 10:10.276
Six days?

10:10.360 --> 10:12.111
I hazard a guess it wasn't a car crash?

10:12.195 --> 10:14.071
Got one body with defensive wounds.

10:14.239 --> 10:15.823
- Appears to have been strangled.
- Jesus.

10:15.949 --> 10:18.492
The other, Ms Edmunds,
had a fatal gunshot wound to the neck.

10:19.286 --> 10:21.412
I think I know the man you're looking for.

10:30.922 --> 10:32.923
Don't take this the wrong way, Jody.

10:33.466 --> 10:35.592
You know I love you
and I think you're a genius,

10:35.677 --> 10:36.969
but you got to get the hell out.

10:37.053 --> 10:38.804
I can't go anywhere, Kennet.

10:39.306 --> 10:40.723
Look at me. I'm in pain, brother.

10:40.807 --> 10:43.434
Just let the meds kick in. You'll be straight.

10:43.518 --> 10:46.729
They kept you well this long.
Then you can go hit up your old lady.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.231
She already messed up my shit.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.066
I got to heal before I can go get with Katrina.

10:51.234 --> 10:52.568
Six days now

10:52.819 --> 10:55.237
you've been healing all over my couch.

10:55.322 --> 10:57.573
- I think you're good.
- Hey, hey.

10:58.033 --> 10:59.158
Pack me a bowl, would you?

11:00.910 --> 11:02.161
I helped out like you asked.

11:02.245 --> 11:04.788
I jabbed the tyres in that van.
I came to your rescue.

11:04.956 --> 11:08.125
But you add two bodies
to the two dope dealers in Knoxville.

11:08.251 --> 11:09.543
That's four killings in under a month.

11:09.627 --> 11:11.211
I'm not cut out for that. I'm a filmmaker!

11:11.463 --> 11:15.007
Let me tell you something
so you can stop your bitch-ass complaining.

11:15.425 --> 11:18.677
I don't want to go
to see Katrina per se, you dig?

11:18.845 --> 11:22.806
I'm gonna go get the goddamn money
I got stashed at Katrina's.

11:23.725 --> 11:25.267
Say what?

11:25.602 --> 11:28.187
Do I have your attention now,
Steven Spielberg?

11:28.271 --> 11:29.396
You left the money part out.

11:29.481 --> 11:32.107
Yes, so you didn't grab it up
while I was convalescing.

11:32.442 --> 11:36.320
So, new deal... I sit a few days.

11:36.738 --> 11:38.697
You take me over. We get the money.

11:38.782 --> 11:41.950
I cut you in 20/80 for your trouble.

11:42.243 --> 11:43.327
How much we talking?

11:43.495 --> 11:44.912
Enough you can finally make your big movie.

11:44.996 --> 11:46.622
- What's it called?
- "The Last..."

11:49.084 --> 11:50.376
Hello?

11:52.128 --> 11:53.337
Yeah.

11:55.673 --> 11:58.092
Well, I... I couldn't say. Not well.

11:58.510 --> 12:01.678
I sold her some stuff on craigslist.

12:02.931 --> 12:04.932
Cameras, lenses, stuff like that.

12:06.226 --> 12:07.559
No problem, deputy.

12:08.353 --> 12:09.728
What was that shit?

12:09.813 --> 12:12.648
That was the police
asking me how I know Sharon Edmunds.

12:12.857 --> 12:13.899
What did you say?

12:13.983 --> 12:17.152
What difference does it make, man?
They know, Jody!

12:19.531 --> 12:21.907
Well, I'm healed. Let's go.

12:28.373 --> 12:29.832
Always hated that house.

12:30.291 --> 12:32.292
Come on, man. Let's go.

12:37.340 --> 12:38.757
Look at that.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.593
Can you believe this? She put in an alarm.

12:42.178 --> 12:44.012
All right, let's go around back.

12:44.556 --> 12:46.598
That's what I'm saying.

12:55.358 --> 12:56.608
Shit!

12:59.696 --> 13:01.280
Katrina's sister.

13:02.198 --> 13:03.323
She's white.

13:03.533 --> 13:05.367
Her sorority sister at Butler.

13:05.702 --> 13:09.204
We are lucky. If she's here, we can get in,
no fuss, no muss.

13:09.372 --> 13:10.706
All right, fine. Good.

13:10.832 --> 13:11.874
Let's make it quick, though.

13:12.834 --> 13:14.960
No, no, no, not that man, not him.

13:15.128 --> 13:17.004
- You know him?
- Know him. I hate him.

13:17.172 --> 13:18.213
Hello, cowboy.

13:18.339 --> 13:20.132
- Who are you?
- Jackie Nevada.

13:20.300 --> 13:23.010
I'm a grad student at UK,
just house-sitting for my girlfriend.

13:23.178 --> 13:26.054
Reason I'm here, Miss Nevada, we have

13:26.139 --> 13:29.057
cause to believe that Katrina's
ex-husband might be coming here

13:29.184 --> 13:30.392
for her and the kids.

13:30.477 --> 13:32.978
He's armed and dangerous and an asshole.

13:33.062 --> 13:35.230
I've met him. You got three for three.

13:36.191 --> 13:37.733
Katrina took the kids to Dollywood,

13:37.817 --> 13:40.152
which, if you know Katrina,
you know is hilarious.

13:40.236 --> 13:42.821
She say where she was staying
or leave an itinerary?

13:42.906 --> 13:44.364
I probably have an e-mail on my phone.

13:46.743 --> 13:49.661
I'm thinking
I'm gonna get my money and kill that man.

13:49.746 --> 13:50.829
- No, no, no.
- No, no, no, no,

13:50.914 --> 13:51.997
it's a good idea, Kennet.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.165
LPD.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.417
Let's go. Come on. We'll get the car later.

13:58.755 --> 13:59.838
Jim.

13:59.923 --> 14:01.173
House-sitter's inside.

14:01.257 --> 14:02.925
I got time. I can get her home,

14:03.009 --> 14:05.677
but she'll give you
all the details on the wife and kids first.

14:05.929 --> 14:07.596
Good. Great.

14:13.895 --> 14:15.270
Are you sure it's here?

14:15.396 --> 14:17.022
Well, I don't know why it wouldn't be.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.608
It's not showing up anywhere else.

14:22.278 --> 14:23.362
Baby.

14:29.118 --> 14:30.702
Mystery solved.

14:31.538 --> 14:32.746
We good?

14:33.790 --> 14:35.958
Look, if I'm being honest, Ava,

14:36.125 --> 14:38.794
I'm just feeling insecure
about this whole thing.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.295
You look grand.

14:40.797 --> 14:42.923
Your hair's combed all nice.

14:44.259 --> 14:46.885
Buttons are straight,
and you got your pocket watch.

14:47.053 --> 14:49.263
They'll look at me if I use the wrong fork.

14:49.764 --> 14:51.932
I don't think we need to worry
about table manners up there.

14:52.058 --> 14:54.726
We just pull them
old horndogs off the women,

14:54.811 --> 14:57.980
we find their history in Harlan, and we see
which one of them could be Drew.

14:58.106 --> 14:59.565
If it comes down to it,

15:00.108 --> 15:02.234
what's a few hand jobs, give or take?

15:02.485 --> 15:04.444
Well, you already looking
for an open relationship?

15:04.571 --> 15:06.446
We're not married yet, Ava Crowder.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.491
Baby, you give
as many hand jobs as you need to tonight.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.243
That's not funny.

15:15.790 --> 15:19.126
Lord, we're going to a rich folk's sex party.
Who would have thought?

15:20.169 --> 15:22.004
How did you know Jody was an asshole?

15:22.630 --> 15:23.964
You two have history together?

15:24.090 --> 15:27.342
A bit. I was with
the people he killed not a week ago.

15:27.510 --> 15:28.677
Did you know them?

15:28.761 --> 15:31.930
Him, no.
Her, I slept with once a year or two ago.

15:32.682 --> 15:33.765
That's sweet.

15:33.850 --> 15:35.017
How is that?

15:35.768 --> 15:38.020
How you're out here getting revenge.

15:38.771 --> 15:41.148
What I'm doing
is making sure you get home safe.

15:42.275 --> 15:43.358
Jackie Nevada...

15:43.443 --> 15:46.194
Sounds like a name
out of a Steve McQueen movie.

15:46.362 --> 15:50.782
My stepdad wanted to call me Sierra,
but he named me after my mom instead.

15:52.285 --> 15:54.661
She walked out on us
before I had a memory of her.

15:54.787 --> 15:57.164
They never married,
and Reno wasn't even my dad.

15:57.498 --> 15:59.249
Your stepdad's name is Reno?

15:59.375 --> 16:02.336
- Yep
- The man's name is actually Reno Nevada?

16:02.420 --> 16:03.545
Some kind of lounge singer?

16:04.255 --> 16:06.590
Card player. Taught me some tricks.

16:06.716 --> 16:08.508
Sometimes we get in games together.

16:08.593 --> 16:10.761
Sounds like you had quite an upbringing.

16:10.887 --> 16:12.346
He did okay.

16:12.722 --> 16:14.264
Best he could without my mom.

16:14.390 --> 16:16.433
I did see pictures
of her posing nude in the backyard

16:16.559 --> 16:17.893
once Reno left on the dresser.

16:18.019 --> 16:19.186
But you never saw your own mother?

16:19.270 --> 16:21.563
Lots of people
haven't seen their moms or their dads.

16:21.689 --> 16:24.191
Yet others do
as much as they can to avoid them.

16:24.734 --> 16:25.901
You just showed your cards.

